1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,687
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,708 --> 00:00:03,040
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,613 --> 00:00:05,890
You two need to save me!

4
00:00:05,930 --> 00:00:08,044
One calls me bad.
The other says I deserve to die.

5
00:00:08,070 --> 00:00:10,573
I've spent my whole life
being resented by you two,

6
00:00:10,610 --> 00:00:12,926
so how could I be fine?

7
00:00:12,963 --> 00:00:15,226
Even iron would fall apart
under that kind of pressure.

8
00:00:15,446 --> 00:00:18,216
You two, am I really that terrible?

9
00:00:19,265 --> 00:00:21,875
I was full of love, even as a child.

10
00:00:22,423 --> 00:00:26,217
I had too much compassion,
so I cried easily. Mom...

11
00:00:27,190 --> 00:00:29,890
She said my soft heart
would make me suffer.

12
00:00:34,095 --> 00:00:35,104
Fine.

13
00:00:35,203 --> 00:00:38,326
I broke the promise we made as kids.

14
00:00:38,376 --> 00:00:39,746
I was wrong.

15
00:00:39,850 --> 00:00:41,745
But can't you stop holding this over me?

16
00:00:42,070 --> 00:00:44,276
Did I ever skip child support or tuition?

17
00:00:44,470 --> 00:00:46,878
Do you have to punish me
for the rest of my life?

18
00:00:47,816 --> 00:00:49,291
That's what I'm saying.

19
00:00:50,106 --> 00:00:53,530
You must be confused, so take some time.

20
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:55,036
I need to think it over too.

21
00:00:55,066 --> 00:00:57,452
There's nothing to think about.
Take responsibility.

22
00:00:57,486 --> 00:00:59,145
Take responsibility for my illness!

23
00:00:59,660 --> 00:01:01,593
How is that my responsibility?

24
00:01:02,190 --> 00:01:04,866
They say people own up to their wrongs
when they're dying

25
00:01:04,896 --> 00:01:06,690
but I guess you can't even do that.

26
00:01:06,790 --> 00:01:08,046
How can you be so shameless?

27
00:01:08,086 --> 00:01:10,520
What does he have to be ashamed of?

28
00:01:10,630 --> 00:01:13,562
Yeong Ju, you hurt him the most
for 30 years.

29
00:01:13,583 --> 00:01:15,020
Thirty years.

30
00:01:15,716 --> 00:01:16,910
Stop it.

31
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:19,104
And what about me all those years?

32
00:01:19,860 --> 00:01:23,763
I lived in hiding like a ghost,
unable to even cry out in pain.

33
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,380
That's my point.
Why did you live in hiding?

34
00:01:26,420 --> 00:01:28,176
Who did you suffer for?

35
00:01:28,226 --> 00:01:29,756
It's just a piece of paper.

36
00:01:29,820 --> 00:01:33,350
- If you'd let it go, we'd all be fine.
- Because it was unfair!

37
00:01:33,590 --> 00:01:36,010
- I was too furious to let it go!
- Enough!

38
00:01:36,506 --> 00:01:39,146
Stop talking about that.
I'm sick of hearing it!

39
00:01:39,943 --> 00:01:41,000
Forget all that.

40
00:01:41,776 --> 00:01:43,324
If you feel a little sorry for me,

41
00:01:43,929 --> 00:01:46,104
bring me anything
that might help with cancer.

42
00:01:46,503 --> 00:01:48,123
I want to live. I don't want to die.

43
00:01:48,216 --> 00:01:50,211
Why do I have cancer
when you're both fine?

44
00:01:50,396 --> 00:01:54,156
You two are stubborn and awful. So why me?

45
00:01:54,456 --> 00:01:55,687
Honey...

46
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:59,363
Do you ever think about people you hurt?

47
00:01:59,810 --> 00:02:01,187
Your parents...

48
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:02,937
and my mother.

49
00:02:03,083 --> 00:02:05,756
They all died in grief because of you.

50
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,979
You never look at what you did.

51
00:02:08,150 --> 00:02:09,930
You only care that you were hurt.

52
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:12,562
It's always you, your way,

53
00:02:12,980 --> 00:02:14,996
and whatever you want.

54
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:17,505
She's right about that.

55
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:21,916
If I were so selfish and so happy,
why would I have cancer?

56
00:02:21,939 --> 00:02:23,030
This is your punishment.

57
00:02:23,683 --> 00:02:24,976
You deserve it.

58
00:02:25,220 --> 00:02:26,833
I don't want to save you.

59
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,479
Even facing death,

60
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:31,730
please reflect on what you've done.

61
00:02:33,476 --> 00:02:34,934
That...

62
00:02:35,724 --> 00:02:37,478
I'm the only victim here.

63
00:02:37,528 --> 00:02:39,146
I'm the only one getting hurt.

64
00:02:39,748 --> 00:02:42,251
I'm the only one being torn apart inside!

65
00:02:42,312 --> 00:02:43,360
Right.

66
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:45,944
How can she talk like that
to a sick person?

67
00:02:45,996 --> 00:02:47,588
She's heartless.

68
00:02:48,573 --> 00:02:50,346
Honey, don't worry.

69
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:52,030
I'll take care of everything.

70
00:02:52,186 --> 00:02:53,800
I'll get whatever you need,

71
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:56,000
and I'll save you.

72
00:02:56,530 --> 00:02:57,946
Honey...

73
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:02,165
Is this really my punishment?

74
00:03:02,525 --> 00:03:04,045
I told you not to say that.

75
00:03:04,130 --> 00:03:05,715
There's no punishment!

76
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:07,635
Fine, one family was ruined.

77
00:03:07,690 --> 00:03:09,562
But another family was born.

78
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:11,262
So it balances out!

79
00:03:12,186 --> 00:03:13,675
You're right. We're even.

80
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:17,688
Just think about us for now, okay?

81
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:22,545
You, me, and Ji Ni.

82
00:03:23,346 --> 00:03:24,479
Honey,

83
00:03:24,563 --> 00:03:27,558
Ji Ni only has you!

84
00:03:27,890 --> 00:03:29,046
Ji Ni.

85
00:03:30,330 --> 00:03:31,810
Ji Ni...

86
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:01,690
(Jungyeong University,
Vocal Music Graduation Recital)

87
00:04:47,363 --> 00:04:48,583
Are you cold?

88
00:04:52,806 --> 00:04:56,006
- There he goes again.
- Give it a rest.

89
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,750
(Samil Bookstore)

90
00:05:26,810 --> 00:05:27,963
Mom.

91
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,392
You look like you've seen a ghost.
Why are you so startled?

92
00:05:31,283 --> 00:05:33,112
You didn't even call.

93
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:36,885
What's wrong with your face?

94
00:05:37,150 --> 00:05:38,858
- Have you been crying?
- Me? Cry?

95
00:05:38,943 --> 00:05:41,208
I'm the one who makes people cry.

96
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:43,260
True.

97
00:05:44,006 --> 00:05:46,270
- You had that contest, right?
- Yeah.

98
00:05:48,277 --> 00:05:49,738
I don't think I'll make it.

99
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:51,650
Sometimes things work out,
and sometimes they don't.

100
00:05:51,683 --> 00:05:54,912
Did you think you'd succeed every time?

101
00:05:54,936 --> 00:05:57,288
That's not what I meant.

102
00:05:58,342 --> 00:06:02,421
- You wanted me to study abroad...
- I think it's a good thing you didn't.

103
00:06:04,430 --> 00:06:05,553
What?

104
00:06:07,643 --> 00:06:08,687
Ji Ni.

105
00:06:09,755 --> 00:06:11,080
Your dad...

106
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:15,896
is sick.

107
00:06:17,363 --> 00:06:18,856
Mom...

108
00:06:38,866 --> 00:06:41,724
Don't cry. We have to stay strong.

109
00:06:44,773 --> 00:06:46,218
What did he say?

110
00:06:46,806 --> 00:06:47,924
Did he cry?

111
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:49,656
Cry?

112
00:06:50,741 --> 00:06:52,342
He told me to be kind.

113
00:06:52,383 --> 00:06:54,276
What? Out of the blue?

114
00:06:54,563 --> 00:06:56,409
Yeah, out of the blue.

115
00:06:57,866 --> 00:07:00,129
He said if he ever leaves us,

116
00:07:01,030 --> 00:07:04,044
I shouldn't fight with you
or be so stubborn.

117
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,937
And...

118
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:08,863
I should be kind to everyone.

119
00:07:10,466 --> 00:07:11,530
Ji Ni,

120
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:14,977
I think...

121
00:07:15,729 --> 00:07:17,869
I've been too hard on him.

122
00:07:20,290 --> 00:07:21,479
What am I going to do?

123
00:07:22,172 --> 00:07:24,266
If he really doesn't have much time...

124
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:25,993
That's impossible.

125
00:07:26,570 --> 00:07:29,447
- I'll ask Dr. Hwang again...
- I called him on the way here.

126
00:07:32,523 --> 00:07:33,983
Don't worry about it.

127
00:07:34,330 --> 00:07:38,253
Doctors always tell you
the worst-case scenario first.

128
00:07:39,113 --> 00:07:40,496
I'm not going to worry.

129
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:42,400
Let's not worry.

130
00:07:42,516 --> 00:07:44,193
We'll protect him.

131
00:07:44,913 --> 00:07:47,466
And don't cry when you see him.

132
00:07:47,893 --> 00:07:49,070
Cry alone.

133
00:07:50,193 --> 00:07:51,553
That's what I came to tell you.

134
00:07:54,076 --> 00:07:55,232
We...

135
00:07:56,206 --> 00:07:57,689
must cry alone.

136
00:07:58,493 --> 00:08:00,476
We have to stay strong for him,

137
00:08:00,793 --> 00:08:03,182
so he doesn't break down.

138
00:08:09,250 --> 00:08:10,437
We...

139
00:08:14,286 --> 00:08:15,436
We...

140
00:08:32,816 --> 00:08:34,830
What are we going to do, Ji Ni?

141
00:08:35,576 --> 00:08:37,059
What are we going to do...

142
00:08:37,466 --> 00:08:39,577
I'm so scared.

143
00:08:41,340 --> 00:08:45,243
What are we going to do
if he really leaves us?

144
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:56,201
You said we had to stay strong.

145
00:08:56,323 --> 00:08:58,193
That's why you came here.

146
00:08:59,306 --> 00:09:00,479
Right now,

147
00:09:01,236 --> 00:09:04,062
he's probably hurting more than anyone.

148
00:09:06,253 --> 00:09:07,360
Yeah.

149
00:09:10,066 --> 00:09:11,694
Yeah, let's not cry.

150
00:09:14,516 --> 00:09:15,646
Let's not cry.

151
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,187
Tomorrow,

152
00:09:17,829 --> 00:09:19,829
he's being admitted to the hospital.
Let's go with him.

153
00:09:19,916 --> 00:09:21,006
Okay.

154
00:09:24,443 --> 00:09:25,646
It...

155
00:09:26,413 --> 00:09:28,315
is all because of Seo Chon.

156
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:31,910
If anything happens to him,
I'll make sure they...

157
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:34,730
pay for this.

158
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:38,806
I'll make them pay for all the tears
and the pain I've suffered.

159
00:09:45,694 --> 00:09:47,760
(Haemyeong University Hospital)

160
00:09:56,293 --> 00:09:57,506
Where's your dad?

161
00:09:58,250 --> 00:09:59,466
He's getting tests.

162
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,708
He's been doing nothing
but tests for ten days.

163
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,375
At this rate, he'll collapse
from all the testing.

164
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:06,749
I told you to stop bringing these.

165
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:08,186
We'll just have to throw them away.

166
00:10:08,291 --> 00:10:10,250
That's why I brought something different.

167
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,298
He should eat something.

168
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,928
Dad, are you okay?

169
00:10:42,471 --> 00:10:43,861
I'm fine.

170
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:47,293
You should go home and get some rest.

171
00:10:51,165 --> 00:10:53,625
Should I wash your hair? You're sweating.

172
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,393
Later.

173
00:10:55,621 --> 00:10:57,415
I'm too tired right now.

174
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:00,333
Okay.

175
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,166
Mrs. Na.

176
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,914
The treatment isn't working at all.

177
00:11:09,958 --> 00:11:11,500
You said this medicine would work.

178
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,000
Why isn't it working?

179
00:11:13,166 --> 00:11:14,375
I'm sorry.

180
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:16,958
I don't know what to say.

181
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:21,158
What can we do now?

182
00:11:29,476 --> 00:11:30,749
Mrs. Na.

183
00:11:30,750 --> 00:11:33,125
It's okay.

184
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:37,552
My husband isn't going to die.

185
00:11:37,833 --> 00:11:39,500
You're wrong.

186
00:11:52,375 --> 00:11:53,649
It's okay.

187
00:11:53,875 --> 00:11:56,291
It's okay. We'll get through this.

188
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,625
We've been through worse.

189
00:11:59,094 --> 00:12:01,375
Of course.

190
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:11,083
Mother.

191
00:12:11,625 --> 00:12:13,833
Stop hesitating and go.

192
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,625
They said there's really no time.

193
00:12:15,877 --> 00:12:16,885
Really?

194
00:12:16,930 --> 00:12:19,500
That Vietnamese tonic
you asked me to find,

195
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:21,208
wasn't it all for father?

196
00:12:21,666 --> 00:12:24,651
Take it to him.
Otherwise, you'll regret it later.

197
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:28,738
They really said there's no time left?

198
00:12:29,458 --> 00:12:32,546
Hospitals don't say that
directly to family.

199
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:35,631
I heard it from a friend
who's an intern there.

200
00:12:35,666 --> 00:12:37,005
A friend?

201
00:12:37,721 --> 00:12:39,346
You sure know a lot of people.

202
00:12:39,375 --> 00:12:42,208
Of course. How long do you think
I've been in Korea?

203
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:44,625
I've got classmates everywhere.

204
00:12:46,041 --> 00:12:50,198
I met Seung Hyun
at the campus post office, remember?

205
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:51,958
O Reum.

206
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:54,680
Your mom went
to Ewha Womans University, okay?

207
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:57,171
Tell me everything you heard.

208
00:12:57,250 --> 00:12:59,225
What condition is he really in?

209
00:13:00,125 --> 00:13:03,166
He doesn't have much time.
Do whatever you need to do.

210
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:05,052
If there's anything to claim,
claim it now.

211
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:07,458
That should be clear enough, right?

212
00:13:15,955 --> 00:13:17,273
So what?

213
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:19,193
Just because that man
has pancreatic cancer...

214
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:21,806
Did you have to show up
at the station over it?

215
00:13:22,041 --> 00:13:24,593
Don't let mom go to the hospital
out of misplaced affection.

216
00:13:24,666 --> 00:13:26,416
She's known about it for a long time.

217
00:13:26,763 --> 00:13:29,054
She just hasn't gone because of us.

218
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,958
This is so frustrating.

219
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:34,449
Being terminally ill doesn't give him
a free pass. Why come here now?

220
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:36,889
He got what he deserved. Serves him right.

221
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,929
- Honestly, it feels good.
- Seung Woo.

222
00:13:38,982 --> 00:13:41,429
What do you even want to hear from me?

223
00:13:41,666 --> 00:13:44,291
Let's go. Let's get an apology.

224
00:13:44,541 --> 00:13:45,916
Don't let him go like this.

225
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:47,583
We both have things to say.

226
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:52,207
Seung Hyun, to me,
you and mom were my father.

227
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:53,515
Let's make him apologize.

228
00:13:53,516 --> 00:13:55,249
At least grab him by the collar
before it's over.

229
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,402
You can do that if you want. I...

230
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:01,291
No.

231
00:14:01,314 --> 00:14:04,172
I don't want to make it easier
for him to die.

232
00:14:04,375 --> 00:14:05,879
Let him die...

233
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,812
with all that resentment in his heart.

234
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:32,916
(KACC)

235
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,416
Yes, this is the final list.

236
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:37,207
Na Ji Ni and Jeon Jung A are tied,

237
00:14:37,208 --> 00:14:39,457
so you can make the final decision.

238
00:14:39,458 --> 00:14:42,291
They attended the same school,
and Professor Bae recommended them both.

239
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:44,666
But Na Ji Ni
has a higher evaluation score.

240
00:14:45,541 --> 00:14:46,582
Then how are they tied?

241
00:14:46,583 --> 00:14:49,207
Jeon Jung A has taken part
in external art activities.

242
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:51,291
Na Ji Ni hasn't done any.

243
00:14:53,245 --> 00:14:55,162
It wasn't that she didn't. She couldn't.

244
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:56,958
We got a report that Na Ji Ni...

245
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,500
was involved in misconduct at school.

246
00:15:00,129 --> 00:15:01,452
We're looking into it to check...

247
00:15:01,485 --> 00:15:03,207
No, we can't take risks
with something like this.

248
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:06,625
It's hard to prove,
and statements can change.

249
00:15:06,666 --> 00:15:08,458
We could end up in needless controversy.

250
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:11,041
- Even so...
- I agree.

251
00:15:11,166 --> 00:15:12,832
People are sensitive these days.

252
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,499
We should take action now,

253
00:15:14,500 --> 00:15:16,250
before it blows up
after her work is displayed.

254
00:15:21,625 --> 00:15:22,833
Really?

255
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:33,375
Yes, I understand.

256
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:36,481
Okay, thank you.

257
00:15:41,958 --> 00:15:43,937
Hey, it's me. You got the call too, right?

258
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:47,270
No, I didn't get a call.

259
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:49,541
I see.

260
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:51,625
Congratulations.

261
00:15:52,799 --> 00:15:54,522
No, your work was great.

262
00:15:54,950 --> 00:15:57,533
Okay. Let's talk later.

263
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:09,000
Really?

264
00:16:09,041 --> 00:16:12,916
Yes, I saved Ji Hu from serious trouble.

265
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,817
Right.

266
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,290
If they'd selected an accused bully,

267
00:16:16,291 --> 00:16:18,550
it could've caused serious trouble later.

268
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:21,500
I'm so glad you warned him in advance.

269
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:25,012
I was quite helpful this time, right?

270
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:26,758
How cute.

271
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:29,896
I'm so glad Ji Hu met you.

272
00:16:32,375 --> 00:16:33,871
Drink this.

273
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,666
Stay for dinner too.

274
00:16:35,708 --> 00:16:37,831
Okay, what's for dinner?

275
00:16:37,883 --> 00:16:40,175
Well, what would you like?

276
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:44,666
Mother, a Vietnamese restaurant
just opened nearby.

277
00:16:44,731 --> 00:16:47,136
- Should we try it?
- Really? Shall we?

278
00:16:47,166 --> 00:16:49,848
Father has plans anyway, so let's go.

279
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:51,598
Okay, let's go.

280
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,814
Ji Hu should hurry up too.

281
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:57,500
He has a job now,
so there's no reason to delay it.

282
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,708
Once Do Hee's parents come to Korea,

283
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:01,606
I'll suggest a formal family meeting.

284
00:17:01,958 --> 00:17:03,582
You're the one I'm worried about.

285
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:06,166
I'm not worried about myself,
so why are you?

286
00:17:06,541 --> 00:17:09,166
You don't know how I feel as your brother.

287
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:12,027
You should have children
and enjoy that happiness too.

288
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:15,208
Will you spend your whole life
just doing acupuncture?

289
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,125
What's wrong with that?

290
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,457
Maybe because you were at sea
when Ji Hu was young,

291
00:17:20,459 --> 00:17:22,221
you're obsessed with children.

292
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,821
I'm not like that.

293
00:17:24,124 --> 00:17:26,831
Don't bother Sun Kyung...

294
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,249
by asking her to find a young woman.

295
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:29,790
I won't build my happiness...

296
00:17:29,791 --> 00:17:31,802
on another family's pain,

297
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:35,124
so don't bring anyone
more than five years younger.

298
00:17:35,125 --> 00:17:36,541
So you still want someone younger.

299
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,133
Why not someone older?

300
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,233
- That works too.
- Hey.

301
00:17:40,791 --> 00:17:43,166
See? Hurry up and lie down.

302
00:17:44,043 --> 00:17:46,291
Enough talking. Hold on. Careful.

303
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,250
Now, Lieutenant No.

304
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:57,256
Your neck is really tense.

305
00:17:57,572 --> 00:18:00,000
I'm fine.

306
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:01,749
I'm used to it by now.

307
00:18:01,750 --> 00:18:03,124
You shouldn't do that.

308
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:06,172
You need to take care of your health
while you still can.

309
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:22,734
I thought you weren't coming.

310
00:18:23,125 --> 00:18:24,734
I wasn't planning to.

311
00:18:27,791 --> 00:18:31,583
You know how to make
my mom's soybean paste, right?

312
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:34,875
I want spinach porridge made with it.

313
00:18:34,916 --> 00:18:36,600
Are you really sick?

314
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:39,207
You're not sick.
Your personality just changed.

315
00:18:39,208 --> 00:18:40,415
Wait until you're sick.

316
00:18:40,416 --> 00:18:42,000
You won't care about pride anymore.

317
00:18:42,792 --> 00:18:46,060
Is it so strange that I want my mom's
soybean paste porridge before I die?

318
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,779
I'll make it for you next time.

319
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,668
For now, eat this.

320
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,833
She says this is a delicacy in Vietnam.

321
00:18:52,204 --> 00:18:53,204
Vietnam?

322
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,668
She's adorable.

323
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,707
Invite her over. Her father-in-law
will give her some spending money.

324
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:01,425
She'd really come.

325
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,470
She loves getting things for free.

326
00:19:04,063 --> 00:19:06,611
Seriously, tell her to come.
Bring O Reum too.

327
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,234
Aren't Seung Hyun and Seung Woo coming?

328
00:19:09,627 --> 00:19:12,207
You've got some nerve. Just eat.

329
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:14,957
I have no appetite at all. No wonder...

330
00:19:14,958 --> 00:19:17,094
I miss my mom's soybean paste.

331
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:20,737
Tell them to come before they regret it
after their father is gone.

332
00:19:23,791 --> 00:19:25,000
Yeong Ju,

333
00:19:27,250 --> 00:19:29,000
why didn't you remarry?

334
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:34,975
What's wrong with you?

335
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:37,242
I was going to come back.

336
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,709
I was going to say it was just a mistake
and come home,

337
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:45,403
- but Ji Ni was born.
- That's enough. I don't want to hear it.

338
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:49,000
You had two sons,
and my father was always on your side.

339
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,490
But I couldn't leave
because I felt sorry for Ji Ni.

340
00:19:57,693 --> 00:19:58,922
Honey.

341
00:20:00,346 --> 00:20:01,700
What are you two doing?

342
00:20:02,509 --> 00:20:06,779
- I...
- I asked what you two are doing.

343
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:10,162
What do you mean?
She brought porridge, so I was eating.

344
00:20:13,845 --> 00:20:16,677
Why would you come here?
What if rumors spread at the hospital?

345
00:20:16,679 --> 00:20:18,670
Is that what matters right now?

346
00:20:19,646 --> 00:20:21,820
Just say she's my little sister.

347
00:20:21,997 --> 00:20:23,523
What?

348
00:20:25,017 --> 00:20:28,216
I feel like putting our family register
on the door.

349
00:20:28,835 --> 00:20:32,054
- Yeong Ju!
- How long will you keep living like that?

350
00:20:32,056 --> 00:20:35,385
Your husband is dying,
and this is all you care about?

351
00:20:35,788 --> 00:20:40,034
- Is this your undying love?
- Ji Ni isn't married yet.

352
00:20:40,468 --> 00:20:43,497
- We can't have another scandal.
- Yes.

353
00:20:43,759 --> 00:20:45,419
Your little sister is leaving.

354
00:20:47,006 --> 00:20:49,503
You have to come again tomorrow, okay?

355
00:20:52,327 --> 00:20:55,752
I have to stay alive so I can handle
the paperwork you've always wanted.

356
00:20:55,754 --> 00:20:59,070
So you're going to hold her hand
and act all sweet just to get it done?

357
00:21:00,592 --> 00:21:03,209
- Just die. You might as well die.
- Hey!

358
00:21:03,211 --> 00:21:04,914
- Hey!
- What?

359
00:21:04,916 --> 00:21:09,005
I wasn't holding her hand.
It just touched by accident.

360
00:21:13,136 --> 00:21:16,088
- School bullying?
- Yes, isn't that ridiculous?

361
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:19,527
Ji Ni was removed at the final stage
because of a bullying allegation.

362
00:21:20,230 --> 00:21:23,194
Your friend is in charge, right?
Can't you look into it?

363
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:28,327
I don't think Ji Ni is the type of person
who would do that either.

364
00:21:28,329 --> 00:21:31,996
- I'd ask her Cheongrok School friends...
- There's no need.

365
00:21:33,068 --> 00:21:35,025
Ji Ni, when did you get here?

366
00:21:36,147 --> 00:21:38,761
I had to get something from the studio
on my way to the hospital.

367
00:21:40,863 --> 00:21:42,930
- Don't look into it.
- What?

368
00:21:43,888 --> 00:21:44,936
Okay.

369
00:21:45,925 --> 00:21:46,925
I'm leaving.

370
00:22:13,873 --> 00:22:15,709
You should've brought O Reum with you.

371
00:22:16,059 --> 00:22:18,001
I miss that kid.

372
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:23,812
He's still young. Mai doesn't like
bringing him to the hospital.

373
00:22:23,857 --> 00:22:25,435
I see.

374
00:22:25,778 --> 00:22:27,390
Her name was Mai, right?

375
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,500
She was cute and pretty.

376
00:22:29,876 --> 00:22:30,922
Yeah.

377
00:22:32,624 --> 00:22:36,595
Seung Woo, can't you at least
show me your face?

378
00:22:36,597 --> 00:22:40,185
- Do you have to turn away like that?
- I came because of Seung Hyun.

379
00:22:40,552 --> 00:22:42,230
He's like a father to me.

380
00:22:44,111 --> 00:22:47,107
Seung Hyun, I'm going.
You said it'd only take a minute.

381
00:22:47,738 --> 00:22:49,029
Seung Woo.

382
00:22:53,751 --> 00:22:55,101
What?

383
00:22:55,878 --> 00:22:58,494
Now that you're here like this,

384
00:22:59,207 --> 00:23:01,228
are you trying to get sympathy?

385
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:03,839
Don't act pathetic.

386
00:23:04,372 --> 00:23:07,675
- You reap what you sow.
- Seung Woo.

387
00:23:08,606 --> 00:23:10,550
That hurts to hear.

388
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:55,797
Please, Ma'am, let me be Cha Ji Ni.

389
00:23:55,799 --> 00:23:57,852
Please, okay?

390
00:23:57,853 --> 00:23:59,897
Ma'am.

391
00:24:01,537 --> 00:24:04,429
Get lost. Who do you think you are,
coming here and causing a scene?

392
00:24:04,431 --> 00:24:07,985
You should never have been born.
You should've died in your mother's womb!

393
00:24:08,877 --> 00:24:10,156
Seung Woo.

394
00:24:12,614 --> 00:24:15,871
- Get out, you filthy brat!
- Stop it, Seung Woo.

395
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,501
Tell her to leave.

396
00:24:24,861 --> 00:24:30,203
Just go. And don't ever come back.
Go live like your mother.

397
00:24:31,906 --> 00:24:38,816
- Go.
- Ma'am, wait!

398
00:25:13,633 --> 00:25:19,689
- Ji Ni!
- Clear the way!

399
00:25:19,755 --> 00:25:21,563
(Emergency Room)

400
00:25:22,051 --> 00:25:23,423
Ji Ni.

401
00:25:23,424 --> 00:25:25,451
The guardian should wait here.

402
00:25:29,516 --> 00:25:31,183
Ji Ni, I'm sorry.

403
00:25:34,028 --> 00:25:35,636
I'm sorry.

404
00:26:01,208 --> 00:26:03,930
They say Ji Ni was cut in the final round
because of school bullying allegations.

405
00:26:07,988 --> 00:26:11,266
You should never have been born.
You should've died in your mother's womb!

406
00:26:11,268 --> 00:26:13,413
Get out, you filthy brat!

407
00:26:14,666 --> 00:26:17,306
Go live like your mother.

408
00:26:18,046 --> 00:26:20,196
You had it easy while I was abroad, right?

409
00:26:20,198 --> 00:26:22,093
A cockroach like you
got to crawl around freely.

410
00:26:22,094 --> 00:26:23,935
Because of brats
born from affairs like you.

411
00:26:23,937 --> 00:26:26,037
- That's not fair.
- And then...

412
00:26:26,038 --> 00:26:28,180
even someone filthy like you
comes along...

413
00:26:28,182 --> 00:26:30,289
They say Ji Ni was cut in the final round
because of school bullying allegations.

414
00:26:30,291 --> 00:26:33,239
You should never have been born.
Get out, you filthy brat!

415
00:26:33,241 --> 00:26:35,307
Go live like your mother.

416
00:26:35,309 --> 00:26:37,663
- Ji Ni was cut in...
- A cockroach like you...

417
00:26:37,665 --> 00:26:39,843
- Because of brats like you...
- Ji Ni was cut in...

418
00:26:39,845 --> 00:26:43,789
- Stop.
- Then someone filthy like you...

419
00:26:43,790 --> 00:26:44,960
Stop!

420
00:26:51,218 --> 00:26:55,716
Hey! If you want to die, do it alone!

421
00:26:58,930 --> 00:27:01,823
Are you okay? You need to be careful or...

422
00:27:04,745 --> 00:27:06,322
Why save me?

423
00:27:07,529 --> 00:27:09,212
Don't.

424
00:27:11,401 --> 00:27:13,194
I don't want to live.

425
00:27:14,135 --> 00:27:16,504
Don't save me.

426
00:27:18,494 --> 00:27:21,225
- Hey...
- Don't touch me!

427
00:27:22,263 --> 00:27:24,378
I said don't touch me!

428
00:27:47,730 --> 00:27:51,097
(Family Register)

429
00:27:51,099 --> 00:27:54,204
You didn't make it, did you?
Your work was good. Why'd you fail?

430
00:27:54,206 --> 00:27:56,280
Apologize and fix this now.

431
00:27:56,282 --> 00:27:57,991
I heard it directly from the victim.

432
00:27:57,993 --> 00:27:59,959
Don't butt in if you don't know anything.

433
00:27:59,961 --> 00:28:01,674
Looks like he regrets meeting me.

434
00:28:01,675 --> 00:28:04,032
If you beg like this,
what does that make Ji Ni and me?

435
00:28:04,034 --> 00:28:06,222
Who are you to refuse an apology?

436
00:28:06,224 --> 00:28:09,856
- Accept the apology!
- Only I get to judge that betrayal.

437
00:28:09,858 --> 00:28:13,266
You said you'd live a long life.

438
00:28:13,931 --> 00:28:15,931
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
